Number of tables in fitness_db

Key Observations

  • The Products table includes attributes like ProductID, ProductName, ProductType, Brand, Price, and StockQuantity.
  • SaleDetails is designed to capture information on individual product sales, linking sales to both Products and Sales tables through foreign keys.
  • Customers table stores customer information including ID, names, email, phone, address, and registration date.
  • ServiceTickets tracks customer service issues and includes references to both Customers and Products.
  • The Sales table records sales transactions, linking each sale to a customer and including details like sale date and total amount.

CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.Products ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductName VARCHAR(100) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC NOT NULL,
      ProductType VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Brand VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
      StockQuantity INTEGER)
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( ProductID );
SQL DDL: fitness_db.SaleDetails 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.SaleDetails ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      SaleDetailID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      SaleID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      Quantity INTEGER NOT NULL,

FOREIGN KEY ( SaleID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Sales ( SaleID ),

UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( SaleDetailID );
